Sorcerer

Target IP: 192.168.182.100

Scanning



There are nine TCP ports open on the target machine. The application on port 7742 looks interesting from the scan above.

Enumeration

Port 7742: HTTP

The login webpage above is displayed for this application on this port. Since I do not have the login credentials, I will perform directory search.


The file tomcat-users.xml.bak contains the Tomcat Tomcat:VTUD2XxJjf5LPmu6 credential above. Where is the Tomcat application running?



There is an interesting directory called /zipfiles. This directory contains four zip files, as shown above. I downloaded these zip files on my machine.


After extracting each zip file, I find max.zip the most interesting. A directory called home exists with interesting files. There is a .ssh directory with the SSH key. Trying to login to SSH with the key did not work as max either.

Exploitation


Looks like a script is run when trying to SSH. This script is included inside the max directory. By the looks of it, commands are only executable if it begins with scp according to the authorized_keys.


I replaced the line 8 scp with bash in scp_wrapper.sh file.

Using scp I transferred the modified scp_wrapper.sh to replace the same file inside the target's max home directory. Now I have a foothold on the machine!

Privilege Escalation


Running sudo -l shows the /usr/sbin/start-stop-daemon has SUID bit set.


And now I have a root shell. GG.
